==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Ichor
<hw>I"chor</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr. Gr.
<grk>'ichw`r</grk>: cf. F. <ets>ichor</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Class. Myth.)</fld> <def>An ethereal fluid that supplied the place
of blood in the veins of the gods.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A thin, acrid, watery discharge from an ulcer,
wound, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ichorhaemia</ent>⟦br⟧
\'d8
